00:24:18.550 --> 00:24:21.680 align:middle line:84%
of objects moving about on their
own, when I was growing up.

00:24:21.680 --> 00:24:26.660 align:middle line:84%
And I really-- it was strange
in the sense that for me,

00:24:26.660 --> 00:24:27.460 align:middle line:90%
it was normal.

00:24:27.460 --> 00:24:29.140 align:middle line:84%
And I had to learn
that it was abnormal,

00:24:29.140 --> 00:24:31.750 align:middle line:84%
and a rather painful
learning as I grew up.

00:24:31.750 --> 00:24:33.460 align:middle line:84%
And my friends would
find it very strange

00:24:33.460 --> 00:24:36.020 align:middle line:90%
that these things would occur.

00:24:36.020 --> 00:24:37.600 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things
that Bohm says,

00:24:37.600 --> 00:24:40.750 align:middle line:84%
because Bohm addresses the topic
of psychokinesis, is, again,

00:24:40.750 --> 00:24:41.950 align:middle line:90%
we don't--

00:24:41.950 --> 00:24:44.608 align:middle line:84%
we may be mistaken to try
to approach psychokinesis

00:24:44.608 --> 00:24:46.400 align:middle line:84%
by saying, what energy
is leaving the brain

00:24:46.400 --> 00:24:47.530 align:middle line:90%
to move the object?

00:24:47.530 --> 00:24:50.680 align:middle line:84%
Because as Bohm says, there's
no division between the objects.

00:24:50.680 --> 00:24:52.490 align:middle line:84%
>> Psychokinesis means
mind over matter.

00:24:52.490 --> 00:24:53.290 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:24:53.290 --> 00:24:55.332 align:middle line:84%
Moving the objects with
just the power of thought

00:24:55.332 --> 00:24:59.820 align:middle line:84%
alone, that we are as connected
to that object as borderless.

00:24:59.820 --> 00:25:01.510 align:middle line:84%
We're a continuum
with the object

00:25:01.510 --> 00:25:03.070 align:middle line:90%
as the patterns in a carpet.

00:25:03.070 --> 00:25:05.250 align:middle line:84%
So for us to move
the object, maybe it

00:25:05.250 --> 00:25:07.000 align:middle line:84%
bumps as just an
act of resonance,

00:25:07.000 --> 00:25:11.590 align:middle line:84%
of realizing that there's
no division between us.

00:25:11.590 --> 00:25:16.930 align:middle line:84%
>> And can we talk for a moment
about the issue of life after

00:25:16.930 --> 00:25:20.340 align:middle line:84%
death or spiritual experiences
of other realities?

00:25:20.340 --> 00:25:21.140 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:25:21.140 --> 00:25:23.343 align:middle line:84%
That's one of the areas
you had mentioned earlier,

00:25:23.343 --> 00:25:25.760 align:middle line:84%
that one of the exciting things
about the holographic idea

00:25:25.760 --> 00:25:28.000 align:middle line:84%
is that people have
taken this and explored

00:25:28.000 --> 00:25:31.150 align:middle line:84%
all different realms, that
some have used it to say

00:25:31.150 --> 00:25:32.500 align:middle line:90%
this is how acupuncture works.

00:25:32.500 --> 00:25:33.958 align:middle line:84%
Because it turns
out that there are

00:25:33.958 --> 00:25:35.620 align:middle line:84%
little micro-acupuncture
systems where

00:25:35.620 --> 00:25:37.670 align:middle line:84%
you can find the entire
body in the acupuncture

00:25:37.670 --> 00:25:38.470 align:middle line:90%
points of the ear.

00:25:38.470 --> 00:25:39.550 align:middle line:90%
>> Recapitulated--

00:25:39.550 --> 00:25:39.980 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:25:39.980 --> 00:25:40.400 align:middle line:90%
>> --in the ear, yes.

00:25:40.400 --> 00:25:41.270 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:25:41.270 --> 00:25:43.630 align:middle line:84%
That we've talked about
the placebo effect--

00:25:43.630 --> 00:25:46.327 align:middle line:84%
some have said that the
holographic idea applies

00:25:46.327 --> 00:25:47.410 align:middle line:90%
in near-death experiences.

00:25:47.410 --> 00:25:49.690 align:middle line:10%
One of these individuals
is Kenneth Ring

00:25:49.690 --> 00:25:51.370 align:middle line:10%
who is at the University
of Connecticut,

00:25:51.370 --> 00:25:53.225 align:middle line:10%
studies near-death experiences.

00:25:53.225 --> 00:25:54.100 align:middle line:90%
And it's interesting.

00:25:54.100 --> 00:25:55.900 align:middle line:84%
Because in report
after report of people

00:25:55.900 --> 00:25:58.382 align:middle line:84%
who have been declared
clinically dead--

00:25:58.382 --> 00:26:00.340 align:middle line:84%
go through some apparent
other level of reality

00:26:00.340 --> 00:26:01.360 align:middle line:90%
and then come back--

00:26:01.360 --> 00:26:03.070 align:middle line:84%
they refer to this
other level of reality

00:26:03.070 --> 00:26:06.190 align:middle line:84%
with terms like frequency
and energy and even hologram,

00:26:06.190 --> 00:26:07.400 align:middle line:90%
that it's a plastic--

00:26:07.400 --> 00:26:09.940 align:middle line:84%
a more plastic level of
reality, where thought

00:26:09.940 --> 00:26:11.440 align:middle line:84%
seems to create
things instantly.

00:26:11.440 --> 00:26:14.320 align:middle line:84%
There are instances of people
having near-death experiences

00:26:14.320 --> 00:26:15.653 align:middle line:90%
where they think they're hungry.

00:26:15.653 --> 00:26:16.870 align:middle line:90%
And instantly, food appears.

00:26:16.870 --> 00:26:18.640 align:middle line:84%
Or perhaps an even
better example--

00:26:18.640 --> 00:26:20.620 align:middle line:84%
when people find themselves
out of their body,

00:26:20.620 --> 00:26:22.120 align:middle line:84%
there are cases where
people look down and see

00:26:22.120 --> 00:26:23.200 align:middle line:90%
that they're in a naked body.

00:26:23.200 --> 00:26:23.980 align:middle line:90%
And they go, oh, my gosh.

00:26:23.980 --> 00:26:24.780 align:middle line:90%
I'm naked.

00:26:24.780 --> 00:26:26.440 align:middle line:84%
Instantly, they
have clothing on.

00:26:26.440 --> 00:26:28.870 align:middle line:84%
Now we don't assume that
clothing has a soul, that it

00:26:28.870 --> 00:26:30.280 align:middle line:90%
has a spirit that survives.

00:26:30.280 --> 00:26:33.040 align:middle line:84%
So somehow, it appears that
the mind can sort of pull out

00:26:33.040 --> 00:26:35.973 align:middle line:84%
of this ocean of frequency
a hologram of clothing.

00:26:35.973 --> 00:26:37.390 align:middle line:84%
And this is what
Ken Ring says is,

00:26:37.390 --> 00:26:40.060 align:middle line:84%
is that we're entering
deeper into the hologram when

00:26:40.060 --> 00:26:42.730 align:middle line:84%
we have near-death experiences,
when we leave our bodies.

00:26:42.730 --> 00:26:45.940 align:middle line:84%
>> So there's so many different
areas that have kind of been

00:26:45.940 --> 00:26:48.940 align:middle line:84%
at the fringes of our
understanding that we can now

00:26:48.940 --> 00:26:51.730 align:middle line:90%
begin to look at with new eyes.

